[Interestingly, no mention is made above of cases of acute encephalitis syndrome (AES) whereas the previous report stated that according to the National Health Mission (NHM) 23 Jul 2019 report, a total of 222 deaths have occurred in the state since January [2019] due to JE and AES. The number of deaths due to JE alone in that earlier report is not given. Currently, the number of JE deaths has now increased to 142. The earlier NHM report further stated that the total number of JE/AES positive cases during this period was 1569. - Mod.TY]

